This is how data travels-

LAYER 1- PHYSICAL LAYER  
Raw bit stream transmission over physical media.
Cables, light, electricity
Cloud version: Virtual NIC drivers.
Physical Security: Hardware tampering, cable tapping, and signal interference.

LAYER 2-DATA LINK LAYER 
Defining data format on the local network.
MAC, Switching, ARP
Cloud: Subnets + ENIs
Internal Threats: MAC Spoofing, ARP Poisoning, and VLAN Hopping.

LAYER 3- NETWORK LAYER 
Physical path selection and routing logic.
IP, Routing
Cloud version: Route Tables, VPC, IGW
The Blast Radius: IP spoofing and routing protocol manipulation (BGP/OSPF).

LAYER 4- TRANSPORT LAYER 
Data transmission via protocols like TCP and UDP.	
Cloud = NACLs/Security Groups
Flow Control: Analyzing the TCP 3-Way Handshake for SYN floods or RST attacks.

LAYER 5- SESSION LAYER
Controlling ports and maintaining sessions.
Port management and session persistence.	
cloud- Sticky Sessions / IAM Roles
Session Hijacking: Exploiting session IDs and port-based authentication failures.

LAYER 6- PRESENTATION LAYER 
Data formatting and encryption/decryption.
SSL Termination / KMS
Encryption Integrity: SSL/TLS vulnerabilities and certificate spoofing.
Cryptographic Failures: Weak ciphers and cert spoofing.

Layer 7 — Application
Human-computer interaction; where network services are accessed.
HTTP, DNS, SSL
Cloud = API Gateway, ALB, etc.
Web Attacks: SQLi, XSS, and API exploitation. This is where the user is the weakest link.



